= Portable GPU mipmaps
Track the work required to make GPU mipmap generation behave consistently across sokol-gfx backends.

[ ] define the public API surface
    keep mip generation separate from sampler state so filtering stays an independent concern
[ ] decide the portable contract
    start with 2D sampled textures, exclude depth, multisampled, compressed, and 3D images in v1
[ ] choose the baseline implementation
    use a pass-per-level raster fallback as the portable path and treat native backend helpers as optional fast paths
[ ] define usage requirements on sg_image_desc
    document which combinations of sampled, attachment, resolve, and storage usage are required for generation
[ ] define update semantics
    clarify whether mip generation happens only after sg_make_image, after sg_update_image, or as an explicit command
[ ] define format rules
    spell out which formats are guaranteed, with sRGB behavior and BGRA/R8/RGBA handled explicitly
[ ] define slice rules
    specify how cubemaps and array slices are generated, and whether they are part of v1 or deferred

= Common runtime work
[ ] add shared validation
    reject invalid image types, missing mip chains, unsupported formats, and read-write hazards with clear errors
[ ] add shared transient view management
    create per-level texture and attachment views without leaking backend objects
[ ] add shared synchronization rules
    ensure generation cannot overlap with render passes, storage writes, or texture reads on the same image
[ ] add shared fallback shaders
    provide a simple downsample pipeline for the raster fallback that covers the guaranteed formats
[ ] decide fast-path selection
    prefer native backend mip generators when available, otherwise fall back to the portable raster path

= Backend work
[ ] GLCORE / GLES3 / WebGL2
    wire up glGenerateMipmap where legal, validate renderable/filterable format constraints, and preserve state cache correctness
[ ] D3D11
    create textures with the required bind and misc flags, then call GenerateMips only when the format and view layout allow it
[ ] Metal
    use MTLBlitCommandEncoder generateMipmapsForTexture on eligible textures and keep encoder transitions correct
[ ] WGPU
    implement the raster fallback with per-mip texture views because there is no portable native generate call
[ ] Vulkan
    use vkCmdBlitImage when the format supports linear blits, otherwise fall back to the shared raster path with proper barriers
[ ] Dummy backend
    keep validation behavior deterministic even when no actual GPU work happens

= Validation and examples
[ ] add a vendor/sokol example that uploads level 0, generates the remaining levels on the GPU, and visualizes mip selection
[ ] test all supported backends
    cover GLCORE, GLES3/WebGL2, D3D11, Metal, WGPU, and Vulkan where available in CI or local build scripts
[ ] add regression coverage
    verify repeated generation after updates, non-square textures, array slices, and sRGB textures
[ ] document backend caveats
    capture the format restrictions and fallback cases so callers know when generation is guaranteed
